cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel technique to stabilize the training of the discriminator in GANs by defining a positive and unlabeled classification problem. It also discusses the theoretical and empirical performance of the proposed model. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GANs are widely used in these fields. The sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.GR (Graphics) are less likely but still possible as they are also related to GANs.
